Package: spatialRegroup
Title: Spatial Regrouping by Attributive Affinity
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(given = 'Nicolas', family = 'Ausello',
    email = 'nicolasausello@yahoo.fr', role = c('aut', 'cre'))
Description: Identifies and reclassifies spatial units such as
    municipalities that are statistically more similar to neighboring
    groups than to their own administrative group. The acronym EPCI
    (Etablissement Public de Cooperation Intercommunale) refers to
    French intercommunal administrative units, used here as an example
    of grouped spatial partitions.
    Computes attributive affinity based on euclidean distance,
    detects border units, removes isolated candidates, and reassigns
    them to the most similar neighboring group.
    Includes tools for multilevel model comparison (AIC, ICC) to
    evaluate whether the recomposed grouping better explains the
    outcome variable than the original administrative partition.
